498
00:35:11,876 --> 00:35:13,741
I'm looking for the Captain.

499
00:35:14,245 --> 00:35:15,371
That's me.

500
00:35:16,647 --> 00:35:18,615
My name's Burt Munro.

501
00:35:21,452 --> 00:35:25,149
I'm supposed to do a job to work
my passage to Los Angeles.

502
00:35:25,423 --> 00:35:27,857
- Yeah, well, I hope you can cook.
- Cook?

503
00:35:30,027 --> 00:35:31,961
- I'll give it a go.
- There's the galley.

504
00:35:36,767 --> 00:35:37,495
Crikey!

505
00:35:38,903 --> 00:35:40,336
Who does the dishes, mate?

506
00:35:41,005 --> 00:35:42,063
You.

507
00:35:47,645 --> 00:35:49,044
Smells good.

508
00:35:49,313 --> 00:35:50,940
What do you have
for us today, Burt?

509
00:35:51,215 --> 00:35:52,978
It's good Kiwi tucker.

510
00:35:55,653 --> 00:35:58,144
Don't let Burt see you
doing that.

511
00:35:58,556 --> 00:36:01,184
Here, don't spoil it
with all that sauce.

512
00:36:01,759 --> 00:36:03,420
- Sorry, Burt.
- Stone the crows!

513
00:36:08,966 --> 00:36:10,160
Are you going to watch
the movie, Burt?

514
00:36:10,234 --> 00:36:12,896
- What's that?
- Are you going to watch the movie?

515
00:36:14,005 --> 00:36:16,337
- What's it called?
- Broken Barrier.

516
00:36:17,909 --> 00:36:20,878
- It's supposed to be good.
- Is Jane Russell in it?

517
00:36:21,679 --> 00:36:23,476
There's a spare seat
over here, Burt.

518
00:36:31,355 --> 00:36:32,287
Smoke?

519
00:36:32,623 --> 00:36:34,989
- No. Not for me, mate.
- You don't smoke Burt?

520
00:36:35,059 --> 00:36:37,391
No, I don't
and that's why people say to me...

521
00:36:37,662 --> 00:36:39,493
how do you keep going
at your age, Burt...

522
00:36:39,564 --> 00:36:41,327
and I say,
well because I don't smoke...

523
00:36:41,399 --> 00:36:44,163
so I'm telling you young monkeys,
don't smoke.

524
00:36:44,802 --> 00:36:47,600
You can laugh,
but my Dad said...

525
00:36:47,872 --> 00:36:49,965
why contaminate your lungs
with tobacco smoke?

526
00:36:50,241 --> 00:36:53,335
The only thing you accomplish with
smoking is destroying your lungs...

527
00:36:53,411 --> 00:36:55,902
- and shortening your life.
- Kill the lights.

528
00:36:59,850 --> 00:37:00,839
Is Jane Russell in this?

529
00:37:02,119 --> 00:37:03,450
Go well, Burt.

530
00:37:04,822 --> 00:37:06,813
- Thanks, mate.
- Not for this.

531
00:37:13,631 --> 00:37:15,155
- Good luck to you, Burt.
- Thanks.

532
00:37:15,433 --> 00:37:17,264
Remember what I said.
Don't smoke.

533
00:37:18,069 --> 00:37:19,001
I'm trying.

534
00:37:19,303 --> 00:37:20,668
Cheerio, mates. See ya.

535
00:37:22,340 --> 00:37:24,638
Welcome to the United States.
Customs to the left.

536
00:37:24,742 --> 00:37:26,300
Thank you, good to be here.

537
00:37:26,811 --> 00:37:27,835
G'day.

538
00:37:34,285 --> 00:37:35,343
G'day.

539
00:37:35,620 --> 00:37:38,088
Please, stand behind the yellow line
until you are called, sir.

540
00:37:38,189 --> 00:37:39,178
What's that?

541
00:37:39,357 --> 00:37:41,791
- Behind the yellow line.
- Yellow line?

542
00:37:52,069 --> 00:37:53,036
G'day.

543
00:37:53,137 --> 00:37:55,571
Passport and customs declaration,
please sir.

544
00:37:56,941 --> 00:37:58,238
There you are.

545
00:38:03,648 --> 00:38:05,843
How long do you intend
to stay in the United States?

546
00:38:06,083 --> 00:38:10,213
However long it takes me to get
to Bonneville and back.

547
00:38:10,454 --> 00:38:12,354
And the purpose of your visit?

548
00:38:12,423 --> 00:38:15,824
To set a land speed record
on my Indian.

549
00:38:16,927 --> 00:38:17,859
Indian?

550
00:38:18,296 --> 00:38:19,422
Mr. Munro...

551
00:38:19,697 --> 00:38:21,688
- So this is your first time to America?
- Yes, sir.

552
00:38:21,966 --> 00:38:24,662
You gave some rather odd answers
to the Officer...

553
00:38:24,935 --> 00:38:26,732
so we just have a few further
questions we'd like to ask you.

554
00:38:26,837 --> 00:38:30,500
- Well, fire away.
- Well, let's go over again what you said.

555
00:38:30,875 --> 00:38:33,605
Now what exactly do you intend to do
here in the United States?

556
00:38:33,878 --> 00:38:35,743
Well, set a land speed record.

557
00:38:36,847 --> 00:38:39,941
- And how do you intend to do that, sir?
- On my motorcycle.

558
00:38:40,251 --> 00:38:43,448
It's in the hold of the ship
at the moment and...

559
00:38:43,721 --> 00:38:48,385
they're going to unload it tomorrow.
It's an Indian, a 190 Indian Scout...

560
00:38:49,260 --> 00:38:50,818
modified somewhat.

561
00:38:51,796 --> 00:38:52,728
You know what?

562
00:38:53,364 --> 00:38:55,594
- I think I've read about your bike.
- Yeah?

563
00:38:55,833 --> 00:38:58,893
Yeah, it was in Popular Mechanics,
a couple of years ago.

564
00:38:59,136 --> 00:39:00,694
That's right, that's me.

565
00:39:00,971 --> 00:39:04,031
A Leslie Hobbs from Christchurch
sent that story.

566
00:39:04,308 --> 00:39:07,038
What was it?
Fastest motorcycle in Australia?

567
00:39:07,345 --> 00:39:09,108
Yeah, and in New Zealand.

568
00:39:11,515 --> 00:39:13,608
Well, I guess you're legitimate,
Mr. Munro.

569
00:39:13,884 --> 00:39:16,580
It sounds like we should be very
honored to have you here in America.

570
00:39:16,854 --> 00:39:19,288
- Well, thank you.
- We're going to give you six months...

571
00:39:19,557 --> 00:39:21,525
that should be time enough
to get the job done.

572
00:39:23,661 --> 00:39:26,027
- Welcome to the USA.
- Thank you very much.

573
00:39:26,263 --> 00:39:27,890
- Good luck, sir.
- Thank you.

574
00:39:35,206 --> 00:39:36,696
- Gears in the trunk.
- What?

575
00:39:36,974 --> 00:39:38,236
Bags in the back.

576
00:39:38,843 --> 00:39:40,174
Bag, back!

577
00:39:40,411 --> 00:39:43,278
Don't worry about me,
I'll do it myself.

578
00:39:43,848 --> 00:39:45,042
Strewth!

579
00:39:58,629 --> 00:40:00,392
Sit in the back, in the back!

580
00:40:00,698 --> 00:40:02,666
- What?
- You, in the back!

581
00:40:04,335 --> 00:40:08,066
Tell you something, mate,
you don't want to get old around here.

582
00:40:11,175 --> 00:40:12,233
Ta ra.

583
00:40:14,912 --> 00:40:16,539
- Where to?
- What?

584
00:40:16,814 --> 00:40:19,112
- Where to?
- Hollywood.

585
00:40:19,183 --> 00:40:22,550
Yeah, I want to go to Hollywood,
I want to see the film stars.

586
00:40:23,053 --> 00:40:25,214
Okay, we go to Hollywood.

587
00:40:25,689 --> 00:40:27,179
Where in Hollywood?

588
00:40:27,958 --> 00:40:31,359
A motel on Sunset Boulevard...

589
00:40:32,062 --> 00:40:33,893
I hear that's a pretty great street.

590
00:40:34,165 --> 00:40:37,134
I don't know who you talking to lately.
Which motel?

591
00:40:37,401 --> 00:40:38,527
I don't know...

592
00:40:38,803 --> 00:40:39,963
a recommended one.

593
00:40:40,271 --> 00:40:42,671
Come on man, what do you think
I am, an encyclopedia?

594
00:40:42,907 --> 00:40:46,604
Drop me somewhere
and I'll sort it out myself.

595
00:40:54,852 --> 00:40:57,047
Must have a bit
electricity bill here.

596
00:41:01,292 --> 00:41:02,589
Firestone...

597
00:41:03,594 --> 00:41:04,652
Shell.

598
00:41:06,697 --> 00:41:10,360
It's all about cars, isn't it?
I've never seen so many cars.

599
00:41:10,835 --> 00:41:14,430
- You say something, man?
- I said I've never seen so many cars.

600
00:41:14,772 --> 00:41:17,070
Got to get around somehow.

601
00:41:21,879 --> 00:41:25,007
Look, there's a bowling alley.
Do you bowl?

602
00:41:31,288 --> 00:41:33,153
What's he honking his horn about?

603
00:41:36,494 --> 00:41:38,894
Jesus!
Crikey, did you see that?

604
00:41:39,997 --> 00:41:41,988
That blokes backing into that
geaser's car.

605
00:41:42,933 --> 00:41:44,457
He's crazy, he's nuts.

606
00:41:45,336 --> 00:41:46,894
He did it again.

607
00:41:48,239 --> 00:41:50,639
Don't stare, there's a lot of
crazy people in this town.

608
00:41:50,908 --> 00:41:52,705
I've never seen anything
like that before.

609
00:42:03,787 --> 00:42:05,914
- This should do...
- What's the damage?

610
00:42:06,657 --> 00:42:08,056
US$8, plus bag...

611
00:42:08,459 --> 00:42:10,256
- US$9.
- What?

612
00:42:11,662 --> 00:42:14,460
Did you just say
what I thought you said?

613
00:42:14,632 --> 00:42:16,759
- Are you deaf?
- What?

614
00:42:16,934 --> 00:42:20,301
- Are you deaf?
- Yeah, I am a bit deaf, but I'm not stupid.

615
00:42:20,437 --> 00:42:23,304
- How much did you say it was?
- US$9.

616
00:42:23,541 --> 00:42:27,910
No, I don't want to buy the cab, mate.
I just want to pay the fare, that's all.

617
00:42:27,978 --> 00:42:29,605
- Where you from?
- What?

618
00:42:29,847 --> 00:42:32,873
- You a British?
- No, you must be joking...

619
00:42:33,117 --> 00:42:35,381
I'm no Pommie,
I'm from New Zealand.

620
00:42:35,686 --> 00:42:37,017
Well, this is America.

621
00:42:37,922 --> 00:42:40,789
And the fare, right there on the meter,
US$9.

622
00:42:41,258 --> 00:42:43,783
Open your wallet
and let the moths out.

623
00:42:44,028 --> 00:42:45,359
I'm doing it, I'm doing it.

624
00:42:46,030 --> 00:42:48,624
There you go, US$9.

625
00:42:48,832 --> 00:42:50,697
- No, don't forget the tip.
- What?

626
00:42:50,968 --> 00:42:53,198
Yes, we tip in America.

627
00:42:53,470 --> 00:42:54,334
Ten percent.

628
00:42:54,438 --> 00:42:56,167
- How much?
- Ten percent.

629
00:42:58,175 --> 00:42:59,642
Oh yeah, there you go, ten cents.

630
00:43:08,285 --> 00:43:09,775
Excuse me, sir.

631
00:43:10,020 --> 00:43:12,045
- You look like a generous man, sir.
- What?

632
00:43:12,289 --> 00:43:14,086
- You look like a generous man.
- Oh do I?

633
00:43:14,358 --> 00:43:17,657
Yes you do. Would you like to buy
a flower to give to someone special?

634
00:43:17,861 --> 00:43:19,920
Well,
sorry I don't have any cash.

635
00:43:20,264 --> 00:43:22,357
Don't worry,
the money goes to a good cause.

636
00:43:22,633 --> 00:43:25,227
It's for an organization
that helps needy people.

637
00:43:25,536 --> 00:43:27,436
Oh alright, well, how much is it?

638
00:43:27,705 --> 00:43:30,037
- Just give what you can afford.
- Alright, well.

639
00:43:31,942 --> 00:43:33,967
They all look the same to me.
They're all green.

640
00:43:34,078 --> 00:43:36,740
- Yes, that's why we call them green backs.
- That looks like a one.

641
00:43:37,047 --> 00:43:38,378
- Look there's one.
- No, that's a ten.

642
00:43:38,482 --> 00:43:40,245
- Thanks, you have a good day.
- No, that's a ten.

643
00:43:40,551 --> 00:43:42,348
Hey come on miss, that's a ten.

644
00:43:42,786 --> 00:43:43,980
I didn't want to pay that much.

645
00:43:44,355 --> 00:43:45,686
Hey, come back.

646
00:43:50,661 --> 00:43:52,094
- Hey baby.
- What do you want?

647
00:43:52,363 --> 00:43:53,660
- You wanna go?
- Go where?

648
00:43:54,865 --> 00:43:57,231
- Go inside.
- I'm going inside.

649
00:43:58,035 --> 00:43:59,866
I'll take you around the world.

650
00:44:00,137 --> 00:44:01,900
I've just come from halfway
around the world.

651
00:44:02,006 --> 00:44:03,667
15 bucks, baby.

652
00:44:03,774 --> 00:44:04,968
15 bucks.

653
00:44:05,242 --> 00:44:07,005
No, sorry, go away.

654
00:44:14,218 --> 00:44:15,116
Hello.

655
00:44:20,324 --> 00:44:23,452
- I need a room.
- A room will cost you five bucks an hour.

656
00:44:23,594 --> 00:44:25,619
I'm planning on staying
a wee bit longer than that.

657
00:44:25,763 --> 00:44:28,425
- How long?
- I don't know, a couple of days I guess.

658
00:44:28,532 --> 00:44:30,659
- Double occupancy?
- What?

659
00:44:30,934 --> 00:44:32,265
Double occupancy?

660
00:44:32,536 --> 00:44:34,936
No, just me, myself and I.

661
00:44:35,706 --> 00:44:38,869
Will it cost a lot because
I can't afford a lot.

662
00:44:40,244 --> 00:44:42,303
- You a member of Triple A?
- What?

663
00:44:42,579 --> 00:44:44,945
- Are you a Triple A member?
- Never heard of them.

664
00:44:45,249 --> 00:44:46,409
Never heard of Triple A?

665
00:44:46,684 --> 00:44:49,881
No Miss Brittle Britches,
I have not heard of Triple A.

666
00:44:51,488 --> 00:44:53,456
Okay, let's just say
you are a member doll.

667
00:44:53,524 --> 00:44:55,424
- Alright.
- That'll save you ten percent.

668
00:44:56,727 --> 00:44:58,695
How does bucks a night sound?

669
00:44:59,129 --> 00:45:01,188
That much? Is that cheap?

670
00:45:02,332 --> 00:45:03,697
Honey, that's cheaper than cheap.

671
00:45:07,004 --> 00:45:09,871
- What's your name?
- Tina Washington.

672
00:45:10,140 --> 00:45:11,334
Well, Tina Washington,

673
00:45:11,408 --> 00:45:13,968
I want you to have this,
it might cheer you up a bit.

674
00:45:14,311 --> 00:45:16,404
Get some of that muck
off your pluck.

675
00:45:16,914 --> 00:45:18,211
Well, thank you.

676
00:45:18,849 --> 00:45:21,079
That's the first nice thing
that's happened round here all week.

677
00:45:21,185 --> 00:45:22,482
You're welcome.

678
00:45:22,853 --> 00:45:25,788
My name's Burt Munro.
From New Zealand.

679
00:45:25,889 --> 00:45:27,379
I'm from down under.

680
00:45:27,691 --> 00:45:29,716
Well, hello, Burt Munro
from New Zealand down under.

681
00:45:30,027 --> 00:45:32,086
I tell you,
I've had a heck of a night.

682
00:45:32,830 --> 00:45:34,422
Welcome to Hollyweird.

683
00:46:26,350 --> 00:46:27,715
Hello?

684
00:46:27,985 --> 00:46:29,213
Anybody home?

685
00:46:31,355 --> 00:46:33,346
- Hello, Tina.
- Good morning, Burt.

686
00:46:33,624 --> 00:46:35,091
You still here?

687
00:46:36,493 --> 00:46:39,291
That's why you were
so crabby last night.

688
00:46:39,530 --> 00:46:40,861
Don't you ever get any sleep?

689
00:46:41,131 --> 00:46:42,564
I work a night shift.

690
00:46:42,866 --> 00:46:45,334
I'm out of here as soon as James
turns up and he's late.

691
00:46:46,570 --> 00:46:49,664
Yeah, could you phone
this number for me?

692
00:46:50,007 --> 00:46:53,374
Yeah, it's a shipping company
and they've got a big box of mine...

693
00:46:53,744 --> 00:46:56,907
and I want to know how
to arrange to get it.

694
00:46:59,183 --> 00:47:01,276
No, you talk to them,
they'll never get my accent.

695
00:47:01,552 --> 00:47:04,020
Okay, what do you want me
to ask them? One moment please.

696
00:47:04,121 --> 00:47:08,785
Ask them when a Burt Munro's box
containing the motorcycle...

697
00:47:08,859 --> 00:47:09,951
will be ready for pick up.

698
00:47:10,794 --> 00:47:13,285
Hello, I'm calling
for Mr. Burt Munro.

699
00:47:13,430 --> 00:47:16,160
Yes, he'd like to know when the box
containing his motorcycle...

700
00:47:16,233 --> 00:47:18,326
- will be available for pick up.
- What ship?

701
00:47:18,936 --> 00:47:21,234
- What ship?
- Rangatira from New Zealand.

702
00:47:21,572 --> 00:47:23,631
The Rangatira from New Zealand.

703
00:47:23,807 --> 00:47:25,468
- It's arrived,
- So he can claim it?

704
00:47:27,578 --> 00:47:29,944
Tomorrow from the Long Beach
customs holding area.

705
00:47:30,247 --> 00:47:32,112
Okay, thank you, I'll tell him.
Bye-bye.

706
00:47:32,482 --> 00:47:33,972
That was pretty fast.

707
00:47:34,351 --> 00:47:35,818
You're late.

708
00:47:38,088 --> 00:47:41,387
I can't stand another minute in
this place. Let me buy you breakfast.

709
00:47:44,862 --> 00:47:46,090
Well, this is great.

710
00:47:46,463 --> 00:47:50,263
You know, I've never seen
a menu with photographs before.

711
00:47:51,535 --> 00:47:53,025
- Are you ready to order, sir?
- What?

712
00:47:53,303 --> 00:47:55,066
- Are you ready?
- Oh yes...

713
00:47:56,306 --> 00:47:59,969
I think the Double Delight,
that's for me.

714
00:48:00,711 --> 00:48:02,474
- How would you like your eggs?
- What?

715
00:48:02,746 --> 00:48:04,270
How would you like your eggs?

716
00:48:05,082 --> 00:48:06,310
Well, I'd like them cooked.

717
00:48:07,284 --> 00:48:10,151
Sunny side up? Over easy?

718
00:48:10,554 --> 00:48:13,785
- I don't know, whatever you recommend.
- Over easy's best.

719
00:48:14,591 --> 00:48:16,115
Alright, eggs over easy.

720
00:48:16,493 --> 00:48:17,619
Make that two.

721
00:48:17,961 --> 00:48:20,555
Over easy.
I must remember that.

722
00:48:20,831 --> 00:48:23,561
Yeah, I like this American
breakfast thing.

723
00:48:24,334 --> 00:48:25,301
It's good.

724
00:48:27,004 --> 00:48:31,373
So my girl, where's the best place
for me to get a used car?

725
00:48:31,642 --> 00:48:32,904
The Valley.

726
00:48:33,443 --> 00:48:35,411
After breakfast I could
take you there.

727
00:48:35,512 --> 00:48:36,479
Oh Well, thank you.

728
00:48:38,582 --> 00:48:40,174
And I'm not a girl.

729
00:48:42,386 --> 00:48:43,375
I'm a boy.

730
00:48:48,458 --> 00:48:50,790
I thought there was something
a little odd about you.

731
00:48:50,861 --> 00:48:53,728
But hey,
you're still a sweetheart.

732
00:48:56,633 --> 00:48:57,531
Yep.

733
00:49:11,715 --> 00:49:12,943
Thanks a million, Tina.

734
00:49:13,283 --> 00:49:15,251
Hey,
there are stacks of cars here.

735
00:49:16,053 --> 00:49:18,248
- I'll be back in the motel later on.
- Bye.

736
00:49:19,556 --> 00:49:20,648
Bye.

737
00:49:26,863 --> 00:49:28,194
How may I help you, sir?

738
00:49:28,532 --> 00:49:32,366
Yeah, I want to buy a car,
a cheap car, a very cheap car.

739
00:49:32,469 --> 00:49:34,630
Well, you've come
to the right place, amigo.

740
00:49:35,038 --> 00:49:39,304
In fact, if you can find cars like this
any cheaper, they're probably stolen.

741
00:49:39,576 --> 00:49:42,909
My name's Burt, Burt Munro
from New Zealand. Nice to meet you.

742
00:49:43,246 --> 00:49:45,737
I'm Fernando from El Salvador,
nice to meet you, Mr. Munro.

743
00:49:45,849 --> 00:49:48,409
- You can call me Burt.
- Alright, Mr. Burt.

744
00:49:48,986 --> 00:49:52,251
So how much were you looking
to spend here Mr. Burt?

745
00:49:52,322 --> 00:49:53,516
Not a lot Fernando...

746
00:49:53,824 --> 00:49:56,418
I haven't got much left after
the cab ride I took yesterday.

747
00:49:57,728 --> 00:49:59,559
You want US$399 for this?

748
00:50:00,530 --> 00:50:02,191
It sounds a bit sick.

749
00:50:02,499 --> 00:50:03,989
Well, what would you offer me?

750
00:50:04,468 --> 00:50:07,335
Listen, I'll give you US$00
if you'll do me a favor.

751
00:50:08,171 --> 00:50:11,004
Through in the use
of your workshop...

752
00:50:11,274 --> 00:50:13,674
and some of that junk
I see lying around...

753
00:50:14,411 --> 00:50:17,039
I've got to knock up
a trailer...

754
00:50:17,481 --> 00:50:19,574
to drag my bike over
to Bonneville.

755
00:50:19,850 --> 00:50:21,818
That's not a favor,
US$35 is a favor.

756
00:50:22,085 --> 00:50:24,212
No, US$5.

757
00:50:25,188 --> 00:50:27,850
You're a tough customer, Mr. Burt,
but I like you...

758
00:50:28,158 --> 00:50:31,423
I'm going to give it to you for US$50
and you can use the workshop...

759
00:50:31,528 --> 00:50:33,894
but only at night
and keep the noise down.

760
00:50:33,964 --> 00:50:34,555
What about tonight?

761
00:50:35,032 --> 00:50:36,522
Yeah, yeah, tonight's ok.

762
00:50:36,833 --> 00:50:40,360
Stop the car, let's get
this thing running properly.

763
00:50:54,284 --> 00:50:55,615
There that sounds better.

764
00:50:57,521 --> 00:51:00,615
- Let me drive.
- Okay, come on.

765
00:51:00,824 --> 00:51:03,224
She's singing
like a bird now.

766
00:51:03,627 --> 00:51:05,754
Oh, she's a good old girl,
isn't she?

767
00:51:06,029 --> 00:51:07,462
There we are, alright.

768
00:51:14,337 --> 00:51:17,602
- You make a left here, Mr. Burt.
- Alright.

769
00:51:21,445 --> 00:51:23,504
The buggers are in the wrong lane.

770
00:51:23,747 --> 00:51:25,180
Stop the car, stop the car.

771
00:51:27,484 --> 00:51:29,418
Turn, turn, this way.

772
00:51:30,320 --> 00:51:31,878
Stop, stop the car.

773
00:51:34,291 --> 00:51:35,986
Keep your shirt on.

774
00:51:38,128 --> 00:51:41,461
- Scoot over, you stupid old bastard.
- Thought I was back in New Zealand...

775
00:51:41,531 --> 00:51:44,022
we drive on the other side
of the road over there.

776
00:51:44,301 --> 00:51:46,735
Yeah? You're going to get
us all killed.

777
00:51:48,271 --> 00:51:51,069
Well, you're not in New Zealand,
you're in America.

778
00:51:51,174 --> 00:51:53,904
- I know it.
- We drive on the right side of the road.

779
00:52:03,453 --> 00:52:06,513
Burt.
Let me give you some advice.

780
00:52:08,625 --> 00:52:11,321
When you're driving,
not only here in America...

781
00:52:11,461 --> 00:52:13,122
but anywhere's around the world...

782
00:52:13,396 --> 00:52:16,593
the driver should always
be in the centre of the road.

783
00:52:17,033 --> 00:52:19,661
In the centre.
If you're not in the centre...

784
00:52:19,736 --> 00:52:22,330
you're on the wrong side of the road.
Okay?

785
00:52:32,149 --> 00:52:34,049
You want this right here?

786
00:52:37,254 --> 00:52:38,346
That's it.

787
00:52:38,889 --> 00:52:39,947
Yeah, good.

788
00:52:40,457 --> 00:52:41,515
Got it.

789
00:52:42,058 --> 00:52:43,821
It's 3 am in the morning.

790
00:52:44,094 --> 00:52:46,961
Yeah, time flies
when you're having fun, doesn't it?

791
00:52:48,064 --> 00:52:51,033
You know, when I told you that
you could use the workshop at night...

792
00:52:51,101 --> 00:52:53,035
I didn't mean all night.
My wife's gonna kill me.

793
00:52:53,603 --> 00:52:56,265
You take yourself off home
and I'll have a snooze...

794
00:52:56,339 --> 00:52:58,899
in the back of the car
and you know, mate...

795
00:52:59,176 --> 00:53:01,440
I'll lock up the place
before I go to sleep.

796
00:53:01,511 --> 00:53:05,038
Seems to me a whole lot of effort
to sell a lousy US$50 motorcar.

797
00:53:05,615 --> 00:53:08,482
Okay, Mr. Burt, you pull the door down.
Have a good night.

798
00:53:09,653 --> 00:53:14,386
Fernando.
Where do I take a leak around here?

799
00:53:15,192 --> 00:53:16,784
- Leak?
- Yeah, a pee...

800
00:53:17,027 --> 00:53:19,052
trouble with the old prostrate,
you know.

801
00:53:19,362 --> 00:53:22,627
Yeah, go straight through those doors,
there's a door there that says Caballero...

802
00:53:23,133 --> 00:53:24,065
Alright.

803
00:53:25,068 --> 00:53:27,059
Well, I'll see you in the morning,
early okay?

804
00:53:27,170 --> 00:53:28,330
Good night.

805
00:53:29,139 --> 00:53:29,901
Where were we?

806
00:53:34,110 --> 00:53:34,735
Burt?

807
00:53:37,013 --> 00:53:38,571
Good morning, Mr. Burt.

808
00:53:42,085 --> 00:53:44,383
- So did you get it all finished?
- Yeah.

809
00:53:44,688 --> 00:53:48,715
All I need to do is find a couple
of wheels and I'll be ready to roll.

810
00:53:49,025 --> 00:53:51,960
Well, you know, I have some wheels
in the back you can have...

811
00:53:52,028 --> 00:53:54,155
- if you just do me a favor.
- Say the word.

812
00:53:57,601 --> 00:53:59,125
Crank her now, Fernando.

813
00:54:00,237 --> 00:54:01,261
Good.

814
00:54:02,872 --> 00:54:03,930
- Burt?
- Yeah?

815
00:54:04,341 --> 00:54:05,365
You're a god damned genius.

816
00:54:05,642 --> 00:54:06,506
Thank you.

817
00:54:06,776 --> 00:54:08,801
Hey listen, why you gotta go?

818
00:54:09,079 --> 00:54:10,774
Why don't you stick around here a while?
I'll pay you well.

819
00:54:11,047 --> 00:54:13,242
Sorry, mate, I've got to get
to Bonneville by the 3rd...

820
00:54:13,516 --> 00:54:17,316
that's when speed week starts and
you know, gotta hit the road.

821
00:54:17,587 --> 00:54:20,613
- Well, you've always got a job here.
- Thanks mate, I'll see ya.

822
00:54:20,957 --> 00:54:22,652
- Best of luck to you.
- Ta ra.

823
00:54:23,827 --> 00:54:25,727
This guy is really good.

824
00:54:37,474 --> 00:54:38,805
Hello, love.

825
00:54:39,075 --> 00:54:40,838
I was worried about you.

826
00:54:41,111 --> 00:54:44,137
Housekeeping said you didn't
sleep in your bed all night.

827
00:54:44,381 --> 00:54:45,939
Do I get a discount for that?

828
00:54:46,516 --> 00:54:47,505
I doubt it.

829
00:54:47,617 --> 00:54:50,051
I need you to show me on a map
how to get to Long Beach...

830
00:54:50,153 --> 00:54:53,020
- so I can pick up my bike today.
- I'm finished here in 15 minutes.

831
00:54:53,156 --> 00:54:54,088
I'll come with you.

832
00:54:57,861 --> 00:55:00,694
Not a bad set of wheels
for 50 bucks eh?

833
00:55:00,864 --> 00:55:03,025
- You sure it'll make it to Utah?
- Yeah.

834
00:55:03,667 --> 00:55:06,431
This old girl will get you
to New Zealand and back.

835
00:55:06,903 --> 00:55:07,995
Here...

836
00:55:08,305 --> 00:55:10,170
- hop in my fair, lady.
- Thank you.

837
00:55:12,809 --> 00:55:15,277
The bloke who sold me this car,
he gave me a good tip...

838
00:55:15,378 --> 00:55:18,643
he said always remember
that the driver, that's me...

839
00:55:18,882 --> 00:55:21,316
should be on the centre
of the road.

840
00:55:21,418 --> 00:55:22,976
- Look out, look out!
- Alright.

841
00:55:23,253 --> 00:55:26,950
In New Zealand we always drive
on the other side of the street.

842
00:55:28,124 --> 00:55:30,183
- You do?
- Yeah, sorry about that.

843
00:55:31,795 --> 00:55:33,023
Do you want me to drive?

844
00:55:33,096 --> 00:55:35,291
No, it's alright,
I have to get used to it, haven't I?

845
00:55:38,501 --> 00:55:40,230
This should be customs
right here.

846
00:55:40,337 --> 00:55:41,326
Right.

847
00:55:47,777 --> 00:55:49,574
- Hello.
- May I help you, sir?

848
00:55:49,846 --> 00:55:53,612
Yeah, my name's Burt Munro and
I've come to pick up my motorcycle...

849
00:55:53,883 --> 00:55:56,443
I came into port two days ago
from New Zealand...

850
00:55:56,720 --> 00:55:59,689
and on a freighter
called Rangatira...

851
00:55:59,956 --> 00:56:02,424
and I was told to come here
to clear it through customs.

852
00:56:03,793 --> 00:56:05,784
- Mr. Munro.
- Yeah, Munro...

853
00:56:06,062 --> 00:56:07,495
M U N R O.

854
00:56:10,367 --> 00:56:12,494
- Wait here a moment, sir.
- Thank you.

855
00:56:16,005 --> 00:56:18,667
Mr. Munro is here
for that damaged shipment.

856
00:56:21,945 --> 00:56:23,879
- Mr. Moonro.
- Munro.

857
00:56:24,147 --> 00:56:26,547
- Come with me please, to the storage area.
- Is there a problem?

858
00:56:26,616 --> 00:56:28,641
Your consignment
has suffered some damage.

859
00:56:29,419 --> 00:56:30,647
Oh, no.

860
00:56:31,221 --> 00:56:34,520
Why the heck did I bother to paint
these arrows on the side of it then?

861
00:56:35,392 --> 00:56:37,883
That's the way it was
delivered here unfortunately.

862
00:56:37,961 --> 00:56:39,292
Well, what happened to it?

863
00:56:39,562 --> 00:56:41,427
My information is that
ten tons of fertilizer...

864
00:56:41,498 --> 00:56:43,295
was inadvertently
loaded on top of your box...

865
00:56:43,400 --> 00:56:45,925
while it was in the hold. If I was
you I'd sue the shipping company.

866
00:56:46,035 --> 00:56:49,368
Sue? I haven't got time to waste
my bloomin' life suing anybody.

867
00:56:49,439 --> 00:56:51,600
Get some of your blokes to pull...

868
00:56:51,674 --> 00:56:54,006
this right side up so
we can get into the motorcycle...

869
00:56:54,077 --> 00:56:56,375
and see what damage
has been done.

870
00:56:57,847 --> 00:56:59,781
Alright, fellows,
let's get it unwrapped.

871
00:57:03,720 --> 00:57:05,017
The tail looks alright.

872
00:57:10,160 --> 00:57:11,957
No damage so far.

873
00:57:13,797 --> 00:57:15,424
Oh no damage at all.

874
00:57:15,765 --> 00:57:16,732
Good.

875
00:57:16,966 --> 00:57:19,867
- Lucky it was packed so well.
- Yes, it's a blimmin' miracle.

876
00:57:22,071 --> 00:57:25,700
Well, the old Indian lives
to fight another day.

877
00:57:32,782 --> 00:57:34,340
Well, thanks a million, Tina.

878
00:57:34,451 --> 00:57:36,919
I don't know what I would have done
without you today...

879
00:57:36,986 --> 00:57:38,613
you're the real salt of the earth,
you know?

880
00:57:39,055 --> 00:57:41,785
Are you sure you wouldn't like
to come home for dinner tonight?

881
00:57:41,891 --> 00:57:43,552
- I can't, love.
- I could cook you a meal.

882
00:57:43,693 --> 00:57:46,287
I've got to get this show on the road,
get out of Dodge as they say.

883
00:57:46,896 --> 00:57:49,023
Okay, my good friend
from Kiwi land.

884
00:57:49,299 --> 00:57:51,267
- You stay in touch, won't you?
- I will.

885
00:57:51,768 --> 00:57:53,133
Here's my phone number.

886
00:57:53,570 --> 00:57:56,130
- Call me and tell me how you're doing.
- I will. Can I call collect?

887
00:57:56,806 --> 00:57:57,966
You can try.

888
00:58:04,514 --> 00:58:07,347
- It's a good job I think you're a woman.
- I am a woman.

889
00:58:07,584 --> 00:58:10,018
Yeah, right. Ta ra love, see ya.

890
00:58:37,881 --> 00:58:39,348
- Morning.
- Morning.

891
00:58:41,751 --> 00:58:43,343
Fill her up, would you please?

892
00:58:43,453 --> 00:58:44,750
Regular or Ethol?

893
00:58:45,989 --> 00:58:47,320
Who's Ethol?

894
00:58:48,124 --> 00:58:49,557
Alright...

895
00:58:50,226 --> 00:58:51,488
I'll take Ethol.

896
00:58:57,667 --> 00:58:59,532
- Hello, young fella.
- Hello.

897
00:58:59,769 --> 00:59:02,237
- Is this a rocket ship?
- What?

898
00:59:02,472 --> 00:59:03,996
Is this a rocket ship?

899
00:59:04,674 --> 00:59:05,800
I hope so.

900
00:59:45,448 --> 00:59:46,540
Oh Gosh.

901
00:59:53,389 --> 00:59:54,981
What's happened to you?

902
00:59:59,929 --> 01:00:00,918
Oh well.

903
01:00:04,601 --> 01:00:06,125
Let's have a look at ya.

904
01:00:22,485 --> 01:00:23,782
Got ya!

905
01:00:26,489 --> 01:00:27,649
Come on!

906
01:00:38,968 --> 01:00:41,163
I thought we were going
to make it you and me...

907
01:00:42,138 --> 01:00:43,765
and now look what's happened.

908
01:01:36,926 --> 01:01:38,791
- Hello, mate.
- Got a problem?

909
01:01:39,062 --> 01:01:40,893
Yeah. Am I glad to see you.

910
01:01:41,197 --> 01:01:45,065
Yeah, I've lost a wheel, help me get
my rig back on the road, will you?

911
01:01:45,268 --> 01:01:46,701
Okay, I'll see.

912
01:01:47,370 --> 01:01:49,429
My name's Burt, Burt Munro.

913
01:01:50,506 --> 01:01:51,564
Jake.

914
01:01:51,874 --> 01:01:53,501
- You Indian?
- Yes.

915
01:01:54,477 --> 01:01:57,503
Well, this here could be
the world's fastest Indian.

916
01:01:57,613 --> 01:01:59,240
Well, at least until just now.

917
01:01:59,515 --> 01:02:01,073
She's a bit heavy mind you.

918
01:02:01,350 --> 01:02:03,875
So let's take it easy,
one, two, three.

919
01:02:05,688 --> 01:02:07,280
Right.
You live around here, Jake?

920
01:02:24,640 --> 01:02:27,200
What do you want to ride
that contraption for?

921
01:02:27,810 --> 01:02:29,277
That's a good question.

922
01:02:31,314 --> 01:02:35,114
Well, I guess the reward
is in the doing of it.

923
01:02:37,086 --> 01:02:40,055
Jake, I'm dying for a pee.
Where do I go?

924
01:02:40,323 --> 01:02:42,223
There's a little building
right there.

925
01:02:42,391 --> 01:02:44,825
I've got a touch of prostrate
trouble now.

926
01:02:45,128 --> 01:02:46,720
I have similar problems.

927
01:02:47,463 --> 01:02:49,363
I thought you blokes would have...

928
01:02:49,432 --> 01:02:51,366
some magic cures
for that sort of thing.

929
01:02:51,601 --> 01:02:52,932
Well, we have.

930
01:02:53,503 --> 01:02:56,802
One old remedy is ground up
dog balls...

931
01:02:57,073 --> 01:03:00,338
- but I prefer prostrate trouble.
- Yeah, I bet you do, mate.

932
01:03:03,880 --> 01:03:05,040
I got you!

933
01:03:06,949 --> 01:03:09,941
Jake, gotta get going,
gotta hit the road.

934
01:03:10,186 --> 01:03:12,746
- Burt, I have something for you.
- What's that then?

935
01:03:14,457 --> 01:03:15,788
What's this?

936
01:03:16,225 --> 01:03:18,284
- For good luck.
- Oh yeah?

937
01:03:18,528 --> 01:03:22,089
I've never worn jewellery before.
Thanks, mate.

938
01:03:22,298 --> 01:03:24,562
I've got something for you too,
hang on about.

939
01:03:26,335 --> 01:03:27,393
Right...

940
01:03:27,937 --> 01:03:29,063
Iet's see.

941
01:03:33,176 --> 01:03:35,644
I've got this, it's a spare one,
I made it myself.

942
01:03:36,479 --> 01:03:39,039
- What do I do with this?
- You got a hacksaw?

943
01:03:39,282 --> 01:03:41,648
Just slice the top of it,
through where the gudgeon pin goes...

944
01:03:41,717 --> 01:03:43,082
and it'll make a great ash tray.

945
01:03:43,186 --> 01:03:45,120
Not that I approve of smoking,
mind you.

946
01:03:45,288 --> 01:03:47,222
- Thank you very much.
- Thanks a lot, mate. So long.

947
01:03:47,290 --> 01:03:50,555
- Sorry we couldn't fix your trailer.
- That's alright, I'll get there somehow.

948
01:03:51,160 --> 01:03:52,252
Burt?

949
01:03:52,595 --> 01:03:53,789
What?

950
01:03:54,130 --> 01:03:55,427
For the prostrate.

951
01:03:55,865 --> 01:03:57,628
Use with water,
plenty of water.

952
01:03:58,334 --> 01:04:00,097
It tastes bad. Really bad.

953
01:04:00,369 --> 01:04:01,836
Dogs balls huh?

954
01:04:02,271 --> 01:04:04,501
Well, thanks a lot mate.
See ya.

955
01:05:06,269 --> 01:05:07,201
Hello.

956
01:05:11,040 --> 01:05:12,337
Anyone home?

957
01:05:20,750 --> 01:05:21,580
Hello.

958
01:05:21,684 --> 01:05:22,912
Hello, there.

959
01:05:25,821 --> 01:05:29,086
I've got a spot of bother
with my trailer, lost a wheel.

960
01:05:30,993 --> 01:05:33,860
- You're not from around these parts.
- No, I'm from down there.

961
01:05:34,697 --> 01:05:37,063
- What?
- I'm from down under...

962
01:05:37,500 --> 01:05:39,525
The other side of the world,
New Zealand.

963
01:05:39,635 --> 01:05:41,500
Southern most city
in the British Empire.

964
01:05:41,837 --> 01:05:43,270
Called Invercargill.

965
01:05:43,506 --> 01:05:45,770
One of the most beautiful
cities on Earth.

966
01:05:46,442 --> 01:05:47,932
Name's Burt Munro.

967
01:05:48,210 --> 01:05:49,541
Burt? Ada.

968
01:05:49,845 --> 01:05:51,039
- What?
- Ada.

969
01:05:52,682 --> 01:05:53,774
There she is.

970
01:06:00,423 --> 01:06:02,618
We got some problems here,
yes sirree.

971
01:06:03,693 --> 01:06:05,558
I tell you what you need to do.

972
01:06:05,661 --> 01:06:09,222
Cannibalize the stuffed axel
out of that old Ford right there.

973
01:06:09,498 --> 01:06:11,329
Lucky for you
I've got some welding gear.

974
01:06:11,400 --> 01:06:13,595
- We'll get a new wheel on there pronto.
- Good.

975
01:06:23,245 --> 01:06:24,473
That's got it.

976
01:06:26,215 --> 01:06:27,512
When you are...

977
01:06:28,651 --> 01:06:29,709
finished there...

978
01:06:30,386 --> 01:06:32,820
I've got something that
I want to show you.

979
01:06:33,155 --> 01:06:34,645
Yeah, what's that?

980
01:06:36,759 --> 01:06:38,158
Never you mind.

981
01:06:38,427 --> 01:06:40,122
You just get that wheel on
there right.

982
01:06:53,442 --> 01:06:55,034
Why'd you bring me out here?

983
01:06:55,311 --> 01:06:57,643
