01:25:42,137 --> 01:25:44,367
- Where do I check in?
- It's just over there.

1225
01:25:44,639 --> 01:25:46,470
- Thanks, fellas.
- Okay.

1226
01:25:48,977 --> 01:25:50,069
I gotta see this.

1227
01:25:50,445 --> 01:25:54,006
Hello, I've come to check in.
Munro, Burt Munro.

1228
01:25:54,315 --> 01:25:55,907
Registration number?

1229
01:25:56,684 --> 01:25:57,844
What?

1230
01:25:58,119 --> 01:26:00,986
Registration number.
I don't see your number here.

1231
01:26:01,256 --> 01:26:04,054
No, it's number 35.

1232
01:26:04,325 --> 01:26:08,159
It's on the side of my motorcycle
over there, that's my lucky number.

1233
01:26:08,429 --> 01:26:09,760
Have you registered?

1234
01:26:11,432 --> 01:26:13,798
No, that's what
I've come over for.

1235
01:26:13,868 --> 01:26:16,166
These two blokes sent me over here,
Mike and someone else.

1236
01:26:16,471 --> 01:26:18,837
Sir, registration closed
last month.

1237
01:26:19,107 --> 01:26:22,440
If you haven't registered,
I'm sorry, you just can't run.

1238
01:26:25,380 --> 01:26:27,075
I can't run?

1239
01:26:28,516 --> 01:26:31,679
Well, how was I supposed to know
I should have pre-registered?

1240
01:26:31,753 --> 01:26:33,880
I've come a heck of a long way
to ride my bike.

1241
01:26:33,955 --> 01:26:36,014
I'm not going anywhere
until I've done just that.

1242
01:26:36,090 --> 01:26:39,025
I've come all the way from New Zealand,
you know. It's a long way.

1243
01:26:39,360 --> 01:26:41,021
Look, mister,
we don't make the rules.

1244
01:26:41,296 --> 01:26:44,697
An event like this doesn't just happen
in one day, rules are rules.

1245
01:26:44,766 --> 01:26:46,666
Entries closed July 31st.

1246
01:26:46,768 --> 01:26:50,431
Well, crikey, I live in Invercargill,
it's half way round the bloody earth.

1247
01:26:51,039 --> 01:26:53,667
How was I supposed to know these things?
I didn't know all this stuff.

1248
01:26:53,741 --> 01:26:54,969
Sir, it's not our problem.

1249
01:26:55,076 --> 01:26:57,670
I thought I could just turn up here
and have my bike timed.

1250
01:26:57,745 --> 01:27:00,270
- You don't have to call me...
- Well, you thought wrong.

1251
01:27:10,024 --> 01:27:12,049
Jim Moffatt!

1252
01:27:12,594 --> 01:27:14,824
It's Burt, Burt Munro.
Can you come over here, mate?

1253
01:27:15,697 --> 01:27:16,959
I'll be right back.

1254
01:27:17,832 --> 01:27:19,424
I need a bit of help.

1255
01:27:19,701 --> 01:27:21,225
Hey, Burt. What's up?

1256
01:27:21,603 --> 01:27:25,232
Well, I have these blokes telling
me I can't run my bike...

1257
01:27:25,506 --> 01:27:27,531
because I'm not pre-registered.

1258
01:27:27,809 --> 01:27:30,300
- You didn't register?
- No, I didn't know anything about it.

1259
01:27:30,411 --> 01:27:32,845
You know how it is Jim,
rules are rules.

1260
01:27:33,214 --> 01:27:36,240
- You should have registered months ago.
- I didn't know.

1261
01:27:37,752 --> 01:27:40,243
I'll have a talk with these guys later,
see if I can change their minds.

1262
01:27:40,521 --> 01:27:43,854
- Your blood's worth bottling.
- I don't know about that.

1263
01:27:44,125 --> 01:27:46,059
Look,
we can talk about this later.

1264
01:27:46,127 --> 01:27:47,856
Maybe you can let him go
through tech inspection.

1265
01:27:48,162 --> 01:27:51,495
Get that out of the way?
Just in case we can let him ride.

1266
01:27:52,367 --> 01:27:54,164
You're asking a lot.

1267
01:27:55,403 --> 01:27:56,427
Alright.

1268
01:28:00,475 --> 01:28:01,999
- Okay.
- Alright.

1269
01:28:02,310 --> 01:28:04,369
- Make me proud.
- Thanks a lot.

1270
01:28:04,646 --> 01:28:06,739
You give me a bit
of a fright there.

1271
01:28:11,486 --> 01:28:14,421
You know these don't look
like high speed tyres.

1272
01:28:14,689 --> 01:28:16,281
Well, they are high speed tyres.

1273
01:28:17,125 --> 01:28:20,390
Look at these hairline cracks,
these tyres have got to be 5 years old.

1274
01:28:20,795 --> 01:28:22,490
- What happened to the tread?
- What?

1275
01:28:22,730 --> 01:28:24,698
I said,
what happened to the tread?

1276
01:28:24,766 --> 01:28:26,165
Well, I cut it off,
that's what happened to the tread...

1277
01:28:26,267 --> 01:28:27,598
I cut it off with a carving knife...

1278
01:28:27,669 --> 01:28:30,035
otherwise it wouldn't be
a high speed tyre, would it?

1279
01:28:30,471 --> 01:28:31,870
What are you talking about?

1280
01:28:31,939 --> 01:28:35,102
Well, you've got to keep the weight in
otherwise when you get to a high speed...

1281
01:28:35,176 --> 01:28:37,406
the centrifugal force will
the tread right off, wouldn't it?

1282
01:28:37,745 --> 01:28:41,647
I run them on 65 pounds of air and
that tyre's safe up to 300 miles an hour.

1283
01:28:41,916 --> 01:28:44,248
I guarantee it. These are high
speed tyres and I made them.

1284
01:28:44,519 --> 01:28:46,384
Well, you're going to have
to replace them.

1285
01:28:46,654 --> 01:28:48,246
The suspension here is
a leaf spring...

1286
01:28:48,556 --> 01:28:49,716
I mean can we pass that?

1287
01:28:50,024 --> 01:28:52,993
Geez, last leaf spring on a motorcycle
must have been in the 190s.

1288
01:28:53,294 --> 01:28:54,591
Well, it is 4 years old.

1289
01:28:54,896 --> 01:28:58,764
- These brakes look completely inadequate.
- Well, I'm planning on going, not stopping.

1290
01:28:58,866 --> 01:29:01,801
Well, the brakes were old
fashioned 40 years ago.

1291
01:29:02,537 --> 01:29:04,266
Is this a hinge of a gate post?

1292
01:29:04,539 --> 01:29:06,598
No, that's from an old kitchen door.

1293
01:29:08,509 --> 01:29:12,172
Let me just ask you what is this?

1294
01:29:12,447 --> 01:29:15,348
It's a cork, what does it look like?
It's a cork from a brandy bottle.

1295
01:29:15,616 --> 01:29:19,985
You know, the thing is it's all about
weight. The less weight, the faster you go.

1296
01:29:20,088 --> 01:29:21,180
And where's your chute?

1297
01:29:21,422 --> 01:29:23,287
- What?
- Where's your parachute?

1298
01:29:23,424 --> 01:29:25,289
I'm not planning on bailing out.

1299
01:29:25,393 --> 01:29:27,759
No wait,
you've got to have a safety chute.

1300
01:29:27,829 --> 01:29:29,228
Well, I can't afford one.

1301
01:29:29,297 --> 01:29:31,925
These forks, if they give out we've
got ourselves some real problems.

1302
01:29:32,200 --> 01:29:34,430
I think I'd have a bit of
a problem that way, wouldn't I?

1303
01:29:35,203 --> 01:29:36,693
- Where's your fire suit?
- What?

1304
01:29:36,971 --> 01:29:38,370
Where's your fire suit?

1305
01:29:38,439 --> 01:29:40,737
Good heavens, man,
I don't intend to burst into flames.

1306
01:29:41,008 --> 01:29:43,169
Always wear me old suit pants
for good luck.

1307
01:29:43,244 --> 01:29:45,303
If they were good enough
to get married in...

1308
01:29:45,380 --> 01:29:47,610
they're good enough to ride
this old girl in and no...

1309
01:29:47,882 --> 01:29:49,941
I tuck the legs of my pants
into my socks like this...

1310
01:29:50,218 --> 01:29:53,312
stop them getting caught
in the chain and Bob's your uncle.

1311
01:29:53,721 --> 01:29:56,019
You've got your suit pants,
what are you gonna wear on top?

1312
01:29:56,090 --> 01:29:56,784
What?

1313
01:29:56,891 --> 01:29:59,826
You've got your suit pants,
what do you intend to wear on top?

1314
01:30:00,094 --> 01:30:04,428
Yes, a black woolen shirt, New Zealand
wool, water resistant, fire resistant...

1315
01:30:04,599 --> 01:30:06,226
and me bash hat.

1316
01:30:06,968 --> 01:30:08,367
Bash hat?

1317
01:30:09,070 --> 01:30:10,002
Yeah, crash helmet.

1318
01:30:10,071 --> 01:30:13,370
You're crazy, you've got to wear
at least a leather jacket on top.

1319
01:30:13,441 --> 01:30:16,672
You put the bike down on the salt,
it's like coarse sand paper...

1320
01:30:16,744 --> 01:30:18,075
it's going to rub
your head right off.

1321
01:30:18,146 --> 01:30:19,841
I couldn't get into the shell...

1322
01:30:19,914 --> 01:30:22,940
with anything bulkier than the shirt on
my back. It's a very tight fit in there.

1323
01:30:23,217 --> 01:30:24,343
Straight out of the ark.

1324
01:30:25,420 --> 01:30:27,388
- What did you say?
- Straight out of the ark.

1325
01:30:27,655 --> 01:30:30,453
Don't be so cheeky.
What's your name, young man?

1326
01:30:31,092 --> 01:30:32,957
McFarlane. Mike McFarlane.

1327
01:30:33,227 --> 01:30:36,253
I knew a McFarlane, he used to sell
milking machines in Timaru.

1328
01:30:36,531 --> 01:30:38,863
You must be related to him
because he was a total prick.

1329
01:30:40,168 --> 01:30:42,159
Look here, you don't even have
a fire extinguisher installed.

1330
01:30:42,370 --> 01:30:46,966
Mike McFarlane used to give me milking
machine parts to make my sprockets with.

1331
01:30:47,074 --> 01:30:48,098
How old are you?

1332
01:30:48,176 --> 01:30:49,837
I don't know,
he was about 35 when I knew him.

1333
01:30:50,077 --> 01:30:51,237
No how old are you?

1334
01:30:51,312 --> 01:30:54,748
His brother owned a general store
down in a place called Bulls...

1335
01:30:55,016 --> 01:30:57,610
- that's a town in New Zealand.
- Sir, your machine is not safe.

1336
01:30:57,952 --> 01:31:00,819
I've been doing this for 43 years
and I'm still here to tell the tale.

1337
01:31:01,055 --> 01:31:04,115
Time's change, we started taking
airplanes instead of riding horseback.

1338
01:31:04,392 --> 01:31:06,189
- Horse power?
- Horse back. Horse back.

1339
01:31:06,327 --> 01:31:07,589
Horse back, yeah.
I got you, yeah.

1340
01:31:08,596 --> 01:31:09,893
You're too old.

1341
01:31:10,331 --> 01:31:13,198
Bollocks. I may have this saggy skin
on the outside...

1342
01:31:13,267 --> 01:31:14,632
but on the inside
I'm still 18 years old...

1343
01:31:14,902 --> 01:31:16,870
and I'll give you a run for your money,
young fella.

1344
01:31:18,439 --> 01:31:19,963
You need some help?

1345
01:31:20,274 --> 01:31:21,366
Hello.

1346
01:31:22,510 --> 01:31:25,377
Rollie Free, Marty Dickerson,
we're a couple of bike fans.

1347
01:31:25,680 --> 01:31:28,581
- Burt Munro from Kiwi land.
- Pleasure, Burt.

1348
01:31:30,985 --> 01:31:32,816
You got me good there.

1349
01:31:33,054 --> 01:31:34,419
Where are you staying?

1350
01:31:34,689 --> 01:31:36,657
That's my salubrious
accommodation...

1351
01:31:36,724 --> 01:31:38,885
I usually sleep at night
in the back seat.

1352
01:31:39,160 --> 01:31:40,821
Salubrious you say Munro, huh?

1353
01:31:41,963 --> 01:31:43,726
We've been hearing a lot about you.

1354
01:31:44,031 --> 01:31:46,090
Sounds like you're cutting
your finances mighty fine.

1355
01:31:46,400 --> 01:31:47,867
Yeah, you could say that again.

1356
01:31:48,135 --> 01:31:50,228
We'll we're up at the Western Ridge,
why don't you drop by...

1357
01:31:50,538 --> 01:31:52,506
it looks as though you could
use a good shower...

1358
01:31:52,607 --> 01:31:55,599
and everybody's staying there and
I bet that there's a spare bed there too.

1359
01:31:55,877 --> 01:31:58,277
Thanks a lot, you yanks
are classic you know that?

1360
01:31:58,513 --> 01:32:00,378
You don't catch me that easily.

1361
01:32:06,387 --> 01:32:07,684
Hey, Burt.

1362
01:32:08,022 --> 01:32:09,114
Hello.

1363
01:32:11,292 --> 01:32:13,192
The front forks could
go at any time...

1364
01:32:13,294 --> 01:32:15,558
the suspension is right out
of the 190s.

1365
01:32:15,830 --> 01:32:18,060
Got hairline cracks all
over his tyres...

1366
01:32:18,165 --> 01:32:21,066
he's got no fire extinguisher,
no safety chute.

1367
01:32:21,335 --> 01:32:24,668
I told you, if it's a time problem, the
old guy's welcome to use some of my time.

1368
01:32:24,939 --> 01:32:27,169
It's not a time problem,
it's a bike problem.

1369
01:32:27,475 --> 01:32:28,874
Well, I think we ought
to let him run.

1370
01:32:29,510 --> 01:32:31,444
He came all the way from
New Zealand to do this.

1371
01:32:31,712 --> 01:32:34,146
Jim, have you had a good look
at his machine?

1372
01:32:34,315 --> 01:32:36,146
All I know is the man's
the genuine article.

1373
01:32:36,417 --> 01:32:38,385
Yeah, but the bike is
the genuine dinosaur.

1374
01:32:38,686 --> 01:32:41,519
Look, we carry the cans
for the decisions around here.

1375
01:32:41,622 --> 01:32:44,557
And if he kills himself and there's
about a 100 to 1 that he will.

1376
01:32:44,625 --> 01:32:47,287
Are gonna have a hell
of a lot of trouble on our hands.

1377
01:32:47,395 --> 01:32:52,094
Yeah, sounds like we're a bunch
of chicken shits if you want my opinion.

1378
01:32:52,233 --> 01:32:55,896
His bike didn't even come close
to passing tech inspection, Jim.

1379
01:33:05,680 --> 01:33:06,374
Burt.

1380
01:33:07,281 --> 01:33:08,680
Hello, Jim. Come in.

1381
01:33:09,350 --> 01:33:11,113
Rollie Free said
I could find you here.

1382
01:33:11,218 --> 01:33:14,119
Rollie Free, he's the best,
he's a real gentleman.

1383
01:33:14,422 --> 01:33:16,788
He set me up in this place
for nothing.

1384
01:33:20,261 --> 01:33:21,353
What are you doing?

1385
01:33:21,862 --> 01:33:25,263
Well, the soft shoe polish
fills in the cracks makes the tyres...

1386
01:33:25,533 --> 01:33:27,660
Iook spick and span,
good as new.

1387
01:33:27,969 --> 01:33:29,436
Cheaper than new ones anyway.

1388
01:33:29,704 --> 01:33:30,830
I didn't see that.

1389
01:33:33,574 --> 01:33:35,542
Well? Can I run?

1390
01:33:38,446 --> 01:33:39,640
I'm sorry, Burt.

1391
01:33:46,921 --> 01:33:48,912
Who the heck
do they think they are?

1392
01:33:49,824 --> 01:33:53,282
Crikey Jim, you know, I'm not trying
to run a mile in four minutes...

1393
01:33:53,427 --> 01:33:56,191
all I've got to do is sit there
and open up the throttle...

1394
01:33:56,297 --> 01:33:59,698
I mean, after all
it's my ruddy life, isn't it?

1395
01:34:00,701 --> 01:34:02,225
Can't you do anything?

1396
01:34:02,303 --> 01:34:06,865
I mean, I just want to try and get her
to go over 00 just once that's all...

1397
01:34:06,974 --> 01:34:08,874
once I've cracked 00
I'll be quite happy...

1398
01:34:08,943 --> 01:34:11,468
to piss off back home to New Zealand
and Bob's your uncle.

1399
01:34:12,146 --> 01:34:16,105
You're a well respected man around here,
can you talk to them?

1400
01:34:16,417 --> 01:34:17,543
I tried.

1401
01:34:18,386 --> 01:34:21,321
You've got as much chance
of writing yourself off as I have...

1402
01:34:21,389 --> 01:34:24,153
you know that.
Just talk to them again.

1403
01:34:25,459 --> 01:34:27,654
I know they'll listen to you, mate.

1404
01:34:30,097 --> 01:34:32,827
Okay Burt, I'll try.
See you tomorrow.

1405
01:34:33,167 --> 01:34:34,225
Okay.

1406
01:34:37,438 --> 01:34:41,067
I mean I'm half the age of some
of those characters out there.

1407
01:34:46,947 --> 01:34:48,380
What's that?

1408
01:34:48,683 --> 01:34:50,378
That's just indigestion.

1409
01:34:56,123 --> 01:35:00,958
Everyone wants us old buggers
to curl up in some quiet corner and die.

1410
01:35:01,962 --> 01:35:05,728
Well, Burt Munro's not ready to finish
yet, I'll tell you that, mate.

1411
01:35:08,369 --> 01:35:10,769
I'll give it a shot
but I'm not promising anything.

1412
01:35:11,505 --> 01:35:13,370
Thanks, mate.
Thanks a lot.

1413
01:35:18,746 --> 01:35:21,681
The famous Challenger One,,,

1414
01:35:31,692 --> 01:35:33,387
What is he doing?

1415
01:35:33,694 --> 01:35:36,060
- Didn't Jim tell him?
- He says he did.

1416
01:35:36,597 --> 01:35:39,327
- Well, then what's he doing here?
- Why won't you let him run?

1417
01:35:39,433 --> 01:35:41,924
Hey, he's too old
and his bike's too old.

1418
01:35:42,236 --> 01:35:44,363
He's come half way round the world
to ride that cycle.

1419
01:35:44,705 --> 01:35:45,865
Yeah, come on.

1420
01:35:46,207 --> 01:35:50,143
- Wendy, if he was to kill himself.
- So? It's his life.

1421
01:35:51,112 --> 01:35:52,773
Keep an eye out
for those officials.

1422
01:35:52,880 --> 01:35:55,440
You sure you want to do this?
I'm not sure it's a good idea.

1423
01:35:55,549 --> 01:35:58,177
Hurry up. If we're going to do
this thing you've got to hurry.

1424
01:35:58,285 --> 01:36:00,219
Alright, let's go,
here's your helmet.

1425
01:36:02,289 --> 01:36:03,551
Here's your goggles.

1426
01:36:03,924 --> 01:36:05,789
- Come on, Burt. We've got to go.
- Yeah, right.

1427
01:36:05,926 --> 01:36:07,450
Come on, put them on.

1428
01:36:12,299 --> 01:36:13,459
Go, go, come on.

1429
01:36:17,805 --> 01:36:19,067
Okay, let's go, push.

1430
01:36:19,640 --> 01:36:21,107
Push, go fast.

1431
01:36:21,408 --> 01:36:22,534
Hey, you can't. Hey...

1432
01:36:23,177 --> 01:36:25,270
- you can't do that.
- Come on, come on!

1433
01:36:26,947 --> 01:36:28,141
Hang on!

1434
01:36:32,920 --> 01:36:34,512
Hey, where are you going with that?

1435
01:36:39,794 --> 01:36:41,762
Stop, stop, stop, stop.

1436
01:36:42,730 --> 01:36:45,790
What the hell are you doing, Burt?
What the hell are you doing?

1437
01:36:46,233 --> 01:36:47,996
Just getting her warmed up, Bob.

1438
01:36:48,068 --> 01:36:49,535
Didn't look like you were
getting her warmed up.

1439
01:36:49,804 --> 01:36:52,068
Jesus, he was going to take
the thing for a freakin' run.

1440
01:36:52,139 --> 01:36:53,197
Bob.

1441
01:36:53,274 --> 01:36:54,263
Oh, boy.

1442
01:36:56,377 --> 01:36:59,972
That is the most determined man
I have ever seen in my entire life.

1443
01:37:00,681 --> 01:37:02,581
I kind of feel sorry
for the old cooty.

1444
01:37:04,218 --> 01:37:05,651
Coming all this way.

1445
01:37:06,253 --> 01:37:08,312
Isn't there some way
we can accommodate him?

1446
01:37:08,422 --> 01:37:10,447
I mean there can't be
much risk there...

1447
01:37:10,558 --> 01:37:13,391
his bike will be
lucky if it does 70.

1448
01:37:13,694 --> 01:37:16,993
What do you say? What if we bend
the rules this once, huh?

1449
01:37:19,500 --> 01:37:20,467
Jesus!

1450
01:37:23,704 --> 01:37:25,262
Bob and I had a little chat...

1451
